      "levels": [{"front": "The weather was beautiful. (past tense — kana appears)", "back": "كان الطقس جميلاً.", "romanized": "kana at-taqis jamilan.", "grammarNote": "Past tense 'to be' = كان (kana). Only present tense drops the verb. كان (kana) = was/were; كانت (kanat) = was (fem.); سيكون (sayakun) = will be (future)."}]
